  "text": "Mac Enteeet al. reported that about two-thirds of the elderly population has poor oral health, but that only about one-third complained of a problem. In their investigation, about half (54%) of the sample identified a problem, and 83% of the subjects were either using a denture with a major fault or were missing a denture [CITATION_1] .",
